A sample dataSet for species_itis 164744

Source: R/sampleData_164744.R
sampleData_164744.Rd

Highly aggregated data. Spatially, the data is from entire extent of fishing reporting area. This is the required format to undergo a laength expansion

sampleData_164744

Format

A dataframe (tibble) with 8 columns

YEAR

year

QTR

quarter year designation

NEGEAR

3 digit NE code to represent fishing gear

MARKET_CODE

2 digit market code

landings_land

Total landings (lbs). From mv_cf_landings

landings_nn

Number of landings (Trips, subtrips). From mv_cf_landings

len_totalNumLen

number of actual fish lengths taken. combined over numLengthSamples. From mv_cf_len

len_numLengthSamples

Number of length samples for YEAR,QTR,NEGEAR,MARKET_CODE. From mv_cf_len

Source

join between mv_cf_landings and mv_cf_len

Data Pull (SQL)

The SQL call for the test data is:

"select year, month, day, negear, negear2, toncl2, nespp3, nespp4, species_itis, market_code, area, ntrips, mesh,df, da , spplndlb,spplivlb, trplndlb,trplivlb,GIS_LAT,GIS_LON from stockeff.mv_cf_landings where (species_itis in ('164744'))"

and is called by:

cfdbs::get_landings(channel,year="all",areas="all",gear="all",tonnage="all",species=164744,species_itis=T)
